<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Napoli president Aurelio de Laurentiis has confirmed that Everton's move to sign Brazilian midfielder Allan will be announced imminently. </p>

<p>The Toffees have agreed a £24million deal for the Napoli man who was also wanted by Borussia Dortmund and Atletico Madrid.</p>

<p>The 29-year-old worked alongside Everton boss Carlo Ancelotti when the Italian was in charge at the Serie A club for 18 months between 2018 and 2019.</p>

<p>Everton are set to complete a deal for Brazilian midfielder Allan, says Aurelio De Laurentiis</p>

<p>The Napoli president confirmed that Allan's £24million move to Goodison Park will be finalised</p>

<p>And according to Italian sports journalist Fabrizio Romano, De Laurentiis said: 'Allan is joining Everton. The deal will be announced soon.'</p>

<p>The Brazil international has been at Everton since 2015 and has made 212 appearances in all competitions. </p>

<p>Allan was part of the side that won this season's Coppa Italia, as Genarro Gattuso's side beat Italian league champions Juventus on penalties in the final.</p>

<p>Everton boss Carlo Ancelotti (left) worked with Allan (right) while he was Napoli manager</p>

<p>Meanwhile, Ancelotti is looking to finalise a deal for another former player in James Rodriguez. </p>

<p>The Colombia international was part of Ancelotti's Real Madrid side in the 2014-15 season and is looking to bring the 29-year-old on an initial loan deal. </p>

<p>Real Madrid know that James has only one year left on his contract at the Santiago Bernabeu but are looking to offload the midfielder's high wages. </p>

<p>Ancelotti also wants to sign Real Madrid's James Rodiguez who he has worked with before</p>

<p>Everton are looking to sign him on a temporary deal before offering him a two-year contract this time next year. </p>

<p>James made just 14 appearances for Zinedine Zidane's side last term, scoring just once. </p>

<p>He spent the previous two seasons on loan under Ancelotti at German giants Bayern Munich. </p>
